## Accessibility

**WCAG 2.1 AA is the non-negotiable baseline** for any DOM/HTML UI layer:
contrast ratios, keyboard navigation, visible focus indicators, ARIA labels
on interactive elements, and `prefers-reduced-motion` support. This applies
regardless of project type.

For canvas/WebGL rendering where full compliance is genuinely constrained
by the medium (a game board that requires sight to play, for instance):
do as much as is honestly possible (an accessible DOM shadow layer mirroring
canvas state, keyboard-operable controls surrounding the canvas, audio cues
as an alternative channel where feasible), and if a specific accessibility
requirement must be sacrificed for the core experience to function, **stop
and confirm with the human before proceeding**, explaining why, and present
the options rather than silently deciding.

