## File Ownership & Dependency Approval

- If you create a file, you are responsible for its tests (where testing applies per the methodology above).
- If you introduce a new dependency, justify it in your response — do not
  install it without explicit approval first.
- If a task requires changes to `/docs/`, update the relevant file before
  marking the task complete.

---

## Agent Roles

> In multi-model sessions, assign models to roles below. In single-model
> sessions, the active model adopts all roles sequentially. This governance
> applies regardless of which model is active in either case.

| Role | Responsibility |
|------|----------------|
| **Orchestrator** | Reads this file, decomposes the task, creates a plan, delegates to roles |
| **Engineer** | Writes logic, components, and integration code — TDD for logic layers, spec-driven for rendering/UI layers per the Testing Methodology above |
| **Tester** | Writes failing tests first for TDD-covered layers, runs the suite, reports failures as explicit tickets |
| **Reviewer** | Final static analysis: memory/resource cleanup, type safety, pattern compliance, Pre-Completion Checks from SKILLS.md |

When switching roles within a session, state it explicitly (`[ROLE: Engineer]`)
so the session log stays readable for oversight.

